 mean removing the USB serial console support and other such stuff.<br /><br />I guess we can't.<br /><br />So new approach:<br /><br /> - screw it. the rq lock is just too central, you cannot call printk<br />from under it. And if you have an oops under it, you're screwed.<br /><br />   Peter, why do you want to try to work from under the rq lock?<br /><br /> - Make a special "debug printk" that is not synchronous. Just make it<br />buffer things, and have it actually print out from a worker thread or<br />whatever. This one *only* takes the lock for that buffer itself, and<br />works everywhere. We could probably even do tricks to make it<br />NMI-safe.<br /><br />   Make code that isn't an oops or other very synchronous "have to<br />print out *now*" aim to use this "softer" printk.<br /><br />Hmm?<br /><br />                   Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
